9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1305, L.D. 1946, “An Act to Clarify the
10 Eligibility of Certified Recovery Residences for Bridging Rental Assistance Program
11 Housing Vouchers”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3012 in the headnote (page 1, line 3 in L.D.) by striking
13 out the following: "Certified" and inserting the following: 'Residents of certified'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3012 in the headnote (page 1, line 3 in L.D.) by striking
15 out the following: "eligible for Bridging Rental Assistance Program"
16 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3012 by striking out all of subsections 2 and 3 (page 1,
17 lines 10 to 18 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
18 '2. Eligibility of residents. An individual residing in a certified recovery residence is
19 eligible to apply for a program housing voucher to be used upon the individual's departure
20 from the certified recovery residence, as long as the individual meets all applicable
21 standards and conditions established by the department for the program. Residency in a
22 certified recovery residence may not be construed as a barrier to application or receipt of
23 such a voucher. This section does not authorize individuals to use program housing
24 vouchers to subsidize the cost of residing at a certified recovery residence.'
25 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3012 in subsection 5 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 24 in
26 L.D.) by inserting after the following: "section." the following: 'In adopting rules, the
27 department shall ensure that individuals being released from institutions, individuals being
28 released from incarceration and homeless individuals have priority over individuals
29 residing in certified recovery residences in the award of program housing vouchers.'
30 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3012 by renumbering the subsections to read
31 consecutively.
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
