COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1305, L.D. 1946
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment clarifies that individuals residing in certified recovery residences may
33 apply for Bridging Rental Assistance Program housing vouchers, but may not use those
44 vouchers to subsidize the costs of residing at a recovery residence. It directs the Department
55 of Health and Human Services, in adopting rules, to ensure that individuals being released
66 from institutions, individuals being released from incarceration and homeless individuals
77 have priority over individuals residing in recovery residences in the award of program
88 housing vouchers.
99 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1100 (See attached)
